title: Studies in European Arms and Armor (History War).pdf
description:
Philadelphia Museum of Art | 1992 | 087633088X | English | 216 pages | PDF | 19.2 MB

This book examines one of the eminent holdings of medieval and Renaissance armor and arms in the United States. Between the years 1982 and 1986, a distinguished group of five internationally respected scholars of armor and arms conducted research on the collection under the National Endowment for the Arts Visiting Specialists Program. Studies in European Arms and Armor presents and disseminates the results of this research
